/* STDLIB/iii/aether/substrate_cli.iii -- iii-substrate: the machine's own
 * algebra, derived from its silicon (ENTELECHEIA, the real crossing).
 *
 *   iii-substrate real            derive THIS machine's algebra from the live
 *                                 cpu_census + behavioral_fp signature; print
 *                                 the carrier, the operation table, and the
 *                                 laws that HOLD (observed by exhaustion).
 *   iii-substrate variance <N>    THE FALSIFIER: sweep N distinct signatures
 *                                 and count distinct profiles.  Exit 0 iff the
 *                                 discovered algebra VARIES with the substrate
 *                                 (>= 2 distinct profiles) -- the evidence it is
 *                                 derived, not authored.  Exit 2 = REFUTED
 *                                 (invariant -> authored); exit 3 = degenerate
 *                                 (no non-trivial law anywhere in the sweep).
 *   iii-substrate atoms           THE ATOM SOURCE: the chip's own capability
 *                                 report (live CPUID) and the term universe it
 *                                 grants -- which instructions exist HERE.
 *   iii-substrate bridge          per gated atom: the LIVE INSTRUCTION agrees
 *                                 with its independent pure-.iii definiens over
 *                                 the whole published battery (two engines).
 *   iii-substrate isa <lawfuel>   THE ISA-BORN LOOP: fairness arm, law sweep on
 *                                 the real silicon (REFUTED-with-witness or
 *                                 SURVIVED-whole-battery), survivors classed
 *                                 (baseline = human-charted, held out; gated =
 *                                 the uncharted axis), reddening control,
 *                                 capability-mask variance falsifier, and the
 *                                 KATABASIS discovery admission -- exit is the
 *                                 admission verdict.
 *
 * Exit: 0 OK/ADMIT | 1 usage | 2 SUBSTRATE-INVARIANT (refuted) | 3 degenerate
 *     | isa: verdict codes 1..6 (atoms-dead / unbridged / unadjudicated /
 *       charted-only / control-silent / invariant) | 7 vacuous | 8 fairness.
 * Hexad: kind_essence.  Ring: R0.  NIH: composes aether/substrate_ontogenesis
 * + aether/isa_ontogenesis + katabasis/isa_admit + omnia/event_substrate.
 */
module substrate_cli

